text:
throughout 2018 sexual harassment has dominated public discourse, both nationally and here in our state. this is especially true at the rhode island state house. in june, ri now spoke out several times on the need for sexual harassment legislation to be seriously considered by the general assembly, especially the sets of bills that came out of the sexual harassment commission chaired by representative teresa tanzi. 
in the wake of further allegations of sexual harassment–related to members of the leadership team in the house of representatives–we again want to emphasize the need to pass legislation that protects all rhode island residents from harassment and discrimination at work. while much of the focus is on gender, other categories like race, religion, and age come under the purview of this work as well. 
we thank representative chris blazejewski for reopening the legislative conversation about sexual harassment, especially at the state house, this week. that said, it is imperative that female legislators be involved in this discussion and not just the predominantly male leadership in the house, which has previously dismissed accusations of sexual harassment.

in particular, we call on house leadership to reconvene the sexual harassment task force with an expanded mission to address state house internal governance on matters related to sexual harassment. as in many other aspects of state house leadership we demand more, rather than less transparency when it comes to these issues. we continue to stand with those who speak out on sexual harassment.

throughout 2018 sexual harassment has dominated public discourse, both nationally and here in our state. this is especially true at the rhode island state house. in june, ri now spoke out several times on the need for sexual harassment legislation to be seriously considered by the general assembly, especially the sets of bills that came out of the sexual harassment commission chaired by representative teresa tanzi. 
in the wake of fuher allegations of sexual harassment–related to members of the leadership team in the house of representatives–we again want to emphasize the need to pass legislation that protects all rhode island residents from harassment and discrimination at work. while much of the focus is on gender, other categories like race, religion, and age come under the purview of this work as well. 
we thank representative chris blazejewski for reopening the legislative conversation about sexual harassment, especially at the state house, this week. that said, it is imperative that female legislators be involved in this discussion and not just the predomitly male leadership in the house, which has previously dismissed accusations of sexual harassment.

in paicular, we call on house leadership to reconvene the sexual harassment task force with an expanded mission to address state house internal goverce on matters related to sexual harassment. as in many other aspects of state house leadership we demand more, rather than less transparency when it comes to these issues. we continue to stand with those who speak out on sexual harassment.

text:
#respetonaman is a nationwide campaign against gender-based violence. the goal of the project is to spark a sustainable movement across the nation to eliminate all forms of gender-based violence in the philippines through campaigning for awareness, empowerment, and policy.

as inspired by the global #metoo, and #timesup movement and thailand’s #donttellmehowtodress movement, it will focus on bringing the issue into the mainstream and empowering women to rise up against all forms of gender-based violence.

in line with this year's 16-days of activism against gender-based violence, #respetonaman will hold a series of events and programs which would include two big forums, an online campaign, and a localized version of the #donttellmehowtodress exhibit.

#respetonaman is a project of the office of  vp leni robredo, un women safe cities metro manila programme, the embassy of sweden in manila, spark philippines, and empower; supported by don'ttellmehowtodress thailand, cindy sirinya bishop, bdo unibank, sanggunian ng mga paaralang loyola ng ateneo de manila, osci (office of social  concern and involvement of ateneo de manila university), and power plant mall.

text:
speechless! honored to share this new and beautiful @nowthisher original feature and interview i gave about empowering women in the arts. grateful to be given this incredible platform to spread the important message of gender equality and girl power! i hope that this video creates a positive dialogue of inclusion, compassion and hope and that girls and boys all over the world can look within and believe in themselves to make a better world built on compassion. 
sebastian mitre and i have worked very hard the past few years developing sokoki studios and our voice to bring social change via the arts, and i hope we can only continue to reach a wider audience and give inspiration towards creating a just and peaceful world. 
thank you does not begin to express my gratitude to the team nowthis for this beautiful video.

now, facebook community go and rock the world with buckets of paint and please share this post. thank you! 
to see full video please go to my facebook page! .

thanks so much for joining us this past monday night for comedy, community, celebration, and haikus at #nastywomen, curated by @laba.nyc alum, laura beatrix newmark. 
alongside our lineup of wonderful women comedians, were @thehaikuguys (and gals) offering free haikus on any subject of your choice. ✨

text:
williamson county, texas — the morning of september 22, 2017, cristopher precopia went to work at a lumber yard in georgetown.

by the end of the day, he was in jail facing 99 years in prison.

but he didn't know why.

why had police come to his work and arrested him? why was he being accused of these horrible crimes? who was accusing him?

she said he broke into her home in temple.

she said he sliced an "x" into her chest with a box cutter.

she said it happened on sept. 20, 2017 around 7:20 p.m.

x 16x9_1542077470470.jpg.jpg
she was his high school girlfriend. the two dated several years earlier, but he couldn't remember the last time the two had contact.

now precopia was facing a felony charge: burglary of a habitation with the intent to commit other crimes. "i had no idea why everything was happening, and i was lost," he said.

precopia was taken to the williamson county jail, where his parents posted a $150,000 bond. then they began fighting to prove his innocence. #metoo #billcosby #liars #falseaccusers

text:
the selfie that saved him

precopia knew he didn't do it. he knew he couldn't have done it.

on the night of the alleged attack, he was with his mother, erin, at a northwest austin hotel about 65 miles from the accuser's home. "i'm thinking, 'this is awesome. by the grace of god, she said it happened on the day when i can say totally, 100 percent, where he was at," erin precopia said.

there were sworn affidavits from several people who were with him that evening.

there were pictures to prove it, and they were posted on facebook. timestamped. geo-located.

an alibi. "most of the time, we deal with gray matters," attorney rick flores said. "it's not normally black or white. but this is one of those cases where i could definitely prove he did not commit this offense." #metoo #billcosby

text:
in the height of the #metoo movement, many women and men are taking to social media to break the silence and share their stories of being sexually assaulted. but the discussion is not an easy one. how can we support and better understand survivors of sexual violence? what is the root of victim blaming tactics?
┈
xian is an hiv prevention educator specializing in sexual health education for young adults. she also experienced cyberbullying and harassment after she opened up about being sexually assaulted by a celebrity and experiencing other forms of sexual violence. despite this cyberbullying, she continues to believe that she has a duty to bring awareness of how sexual violence and intersectionality can divide, or bring together, communities.
┈
@xianbass has an important message to share at our tedxabqwomen event about the #victimblaming and #cyberbullying backlash that too often follow survivors of sexual assault that decide to share their story.
┈
will you show up and join the conversation on november 29th? get your tickets now! (link in bio)
┈
#showingup #abqshowsup #tedx #tedxabq #tedxabqwomen #strongwomen #abq #albuquerque #nm #empowerwomen #girlpower

text: censorship is all around us, from social media to television to academia to government institutions. what is hidden and blocked from view reveals the cultural norms that override expression and - subsequently - artists' efforts to contest such norms. alison stinely's art was censored before finding a place at the linda matney art gallery. women artists, like stinely, have had their ideas blocked by institutions for centuries. how does her experience with censorship fit within the era of the #metoo movement? what does the silencing of female expression in today's culture mean for women? alison stinely, diana blanchard gross, vittorio colaizzi, lita tirak and john lee matney held a rigorous panel discussion at the linda matney art gallery on saturday, may 19th, 2018 stinely] and her proxies refuse to be labeled, restricted, or contained and possess an otherworldly strength beyond the surface of shiny broken fragments." -dr. margaret richardson. director@lindamatneygallery.com  #williamsburgva  #newportnewsva #norfolkva #odu #artcollection  #757art #richmondva #erie  #malenude #figurativepainting #maleandfemale #3dprinting #florence  #mixedmedia #rva #artmuseum #acrylicpainting #investmentart #censored #sculpture #gilded #popsurrealism #oilpainting #femaleartist #paintings #artist #narrativeart

text:
the easiest thing on earth is to google stuff. looking into the internet for something that you don’t know about is simple, quick and accessible for a great part of the human race. information is there. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
here’s a definition:
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
“ rape culture is a sociological concept for a setting in which rape is pervasive and normalized due to societal attitudes about gender and sexuality.[1][2] behaviors commonly associated with rape culture include victim blaming, slut-shaming, sexual objectification, trivializing rape, denial of widespread rape, refusing to acknowledge the harm caused by some forms of sexual violence, or some combination of these. entire societies have been alleged to be rape cultures”
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i can’t believe it when people deny the existence of rape culture. 
i can’t believe when people get mad about #metoo movement and say things like “it’s an internet thing, people are desperate for attention” ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
one thing is certain we are desperate for attention. that’s right. all the pain that involves to stand up and talk about this reality is worth it when we acknowledge that we are not the only ones and our history is part of a bigger picture.
we will never been silenced again.
hear us fucking roar.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
everyone who is still denying the importance of addressing rape culture is part of the problem.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
to the little girl in the flowers, 🌼
would you even understand what it is i have to say to you? would you remember it? would you believe me?
to the little girl in the flowers, 🌼
you don't quite yet grasp the concept of insecurity, of doubt, of self-judgement. "can't" isn't a word in your vocabulary. you wrote & composed a song in a day, you rode in a plane by yourself, you were a master artist, singer, photographer, model, pianist, fisher, gardner, dancer, mountain climber, and anything else you put your mind too. 
to the little girl in the flowers, 🌼
i wish i could shield you against what you will go through, but maybe it's necessary. it's better to think it is, anyways.
to the little girl in the flowers, 🌼
you will be thrown into the fire. you will know fear, abandonment, isolation, abuse, betrayal, assault. you will stare death in the face and tell him you are not afraid. you will fight him off, you will win, you will survive.
you will be burned. you will douse the flames with an ocean of tears. you will watch the ashes of yourself float away . you will despise the crumbling form in the mirror. 
to the little girl in the flowers, 🌼
you will try to burn those that get too close, you will become smoldering embers. you will desperately try to reignite the fire, terrified that if it dies, you will too.
you will break. you will think dreams are just wishes, and that wishes don't come true.  you will think you are not worthy of dreams, wishes. or stars. 
to the little girl in the flowers, 🌼
you will realize that you were right all along. you are a master of whatever you focus on. you are the creator of your destiny. you are worthy of love, of happiness, of dreams, you are worthy of the stars. you will know confidence. you will become inspiration. 
to the little girl in the flowers, 🌼
you are brilliant. you are beautiful. you are worth everything you desire. 
to the little girl in the flowers, 🌼
i fucking love you.
.
.

#survivor #metoo #youareworthy
#mentalhealth #selfesteem #selfworth #worthy
.

text:
often we underestimate our own strength. and we don't know how strong we are until find ourselves in a situation where we need to muster all strength possible.

our struggles can feel like mountains, and our strength can feel like a small pebble. time and time again i have shown myself that i am stronger than i feel and think. and so are you. tell that mountain to move, and give yourself more compassion, patience and love.

still a queen 👑✊.
.
.
.
#dailyaffirmations #affirmationoftheday

text:
often when we hear about cases of abuse we get caught up in a framework of crime and punishment - “did he do it?” is she lying?” we forget that these are real people, that every case involves someone laying their vulnerabilities out bare.
. 
we are too caught up in “justice”, to convict or not. every witness is unique in perspective, so there will always be different accounts of what happened. what is known for certain however, is that the survivor has experienced harm. while you can argue how reasonable these feelings are, you can not say that someone hasn’t felt harm; that is up to the individual. given this, we should be instead asking the question, what’s the best way to heal?
. 
the reality is that this may not be found in incarceration. is a prosecution that results in sending the perpetrator to jail but retraumatises a survivor really a success? restoration comes from accountability of the perpetrator, to say, “yes i have harmed you and i am trying to change." it comes from asking what the survivor’s needs are, and providing psychological support for their own unique way of healing. . 
we should be thinking about harm reduction and healing, not winning and losing.
. -----
. 
i had the honor of hearing tarana burke, the founder of the #metoo movement speak recently. she answered questions and addressed criticisms about the movement, reiterating what her organization is about.
.
.
#taranaburke #taranaburkemetoo #metoomovement #artistactivist #creativeactivism #socialactivism #consciousliving #creativetones

text:
i started a new job this week, it was time for a change. i decided instead of being awkward and lonely, why not make some new friends? i decided to sit next to someone at lunch that i briefly met during orientation. we began to make small talk, but then he asked me what i was doing prior to joining this company. i wasn’t comfortable telling everyone i worked at planned parenthood, so i definitely wasn’t comfortable telling this stranger. but something in me thought nah, don’t censor it. be proud. so i told him about my previous job. 
he said “what’s that, sounds familiar.” i responded “come on, you have to know, it’s all over the news”. he says “oh abortion clinic, right?” frustrated, i shake my head and contemplate getting up and leaving. but i sat there and explained that planned parenthood is much more than that. they provide services like birth control, std testing, emergency contraception, pregnancy tests, prenatal services, and much more. according to the 2013-14 annual report, abortions only make up about 3% of all planned parenthood health services. 
i’m sharing this story because i believe planned parenthood is a great resource that everyone should be taking advantage of. they provide so many services while being affordable. it’s really important to learn about all the available services for your healthcare needs. don’t let misconceptions about planned parenthood stop you from receiving their services. 
feel free to email or dm us if you have any questions or want to learn more!
#unveilthetruth #thescarletjournal
name: The Scarlet Journal

text:
by alyssa newcomb

beyoncé is cutting ties with philip green, the embattled british billionaire with whom she partnered for her sportswear line ivy park, after he was accused in the u.k. of a series of sexual harassment and racial abuse charges.

the singer's company, parkwood entertainment, said in a statement on thursday that it has acquired 100 percent of the athleisure clothing line.

the decision to take sole ownership of the brand comes “after discussions of almost a year,” according to the statement, predating green’s current troubles.

after an eight-month investigation, britain's daily telegraph published a story last month called “the british #metoo scandal which cannot be revealed." the newspaper said a court injunction prevented it from naming the businessman or reporting the details of his alleged behavior and how he used non-disclosure agreements to buy the silence of his accusers.
name: Pretty Paparazzi

text: #metoo was a movement that spread quickly across hollywood and the media. however, sexual harassment doesn’t just happen in hollywood. there are hundreds and thousands and maybe even millions of people of every gender across the united states alone who have experienced sexual harassment in their workplace. we like to bring this point up because it is frustrating at times to hear of all the harassment cases in hollywood but not mentioning the cases in other jobs and careers—not to mention many do not have the privilege to speak out. we’d like to send our support to those working in hospitals, offices, or restaurants who have been victims of harassment. we’d like to say thank you to those who have spoken of their experiences and send love to those who are still struggling with what they’ve faced. #metoo needs to allow more than just actors to tell their stories. 📸: carell smith

text: for her last exhibit, “cosmic crisis,” @stephaniecortazzo — a ny based multi-media artist— creates a pictorial language of anathema, abjection, and gendered violence to produce a discourse on the bankruptcy of love. her dystopic renderings on modern romance rattled heads at the brooklyn collage collective’s group show in bushwick this past summer. in our exclusive interview by monica z, cortazzo speaks about the process behind her exhibit and the feminist dialogue she hopes to facilitate with audiences. read more at feministwednesday.com 💖#feminist #womeninfilm #feminism #timesup #metoo #feministaf #feministwednesday #vivalabeaver #girlboss #letsgo #bettythebeaver #wednesdayvibes #mybodymychoice #feminista #getitgirl #whorinstheworld #beavertalk #resist #wcw #humpday #girlpower #empowerment #inspo #wednesday #slayallday #woot #letsgogirls #nyc #brooklyn #startup

text_retweet:
#repost from @ibunia
.
we are entering the second edition of 16 film festival in conjunction with #16daysofactivism in the global movement to fight gender based violence. we hope to elevate the consciousness level and the courage through our 16 feature and 16 short films in our line up this year.
.
film adalah media yang ampuh untuk menggambarkan kejadian kejadian dalam masyarakat kita yang kerap bersentuhan dengan kekerasan berbasis gender dan seksualitas. lewat film kita melihat, mendengar, menumbuhkan rasa empati yang tak jarang berujung pada tumbuhnya kekuatan kolektif untuk mencari solusi dan memberantas kekerasan berbasis gender & seksualitas ini.

16 film festival terus berupaya membangun ruang ruang aman untuk berdidkusi, berekspresi, mencurahkan isi hati dan menciptakan support group yang memperkuat kesadaran kemanusiaan. 
meningkatnya angka kekerasan di negri ini memang memprihatinkan. tapi, bukan hal yang tidak mungkin, bahwa kenaikan angka tersebut diakibatkan kesadaran dan keberanian yang tumbuh sehingga setiap kasus meningkatkan kepedulian bersama.

saat ini keberpihakan pada korban lah yang harus diperjuangkan pada aparat dan institusi institusi formil. ruang 16 film festival pun terbuka bagi mereka-mereka yg duduk pada posisi krusial penegakan hukum negri ini.

ayo beranjak, dan turut hadir di 16 film festival! mulai tgl 25 mov -10 desember. hari ini kita akan jumpa pers dulu di @soulfood.id follow @enambelasffest untuk updatenya.
.

text:
the 4th oil that comes in your starter kit is thieves! if there is anything you know about young living it’s probably thieves! it’s the immune powerhouse oil that is the main component in our wellness rollers and cleaning line! “thieves is a powerful combination of clove, lemon, cinnamon, eucalyptus radiata, and rosemary. inspired by the legend of four 15th-century french thieves who used this combination of ingredients to cover themselves for immunity while robbing the dead and dying. “ straight from our fearless leader @grapefruitandgold! how amazing is that?! so how do we use it? use it along with lemon and frank to make a wellness roller. we use this roller everyday especially around this time of year to boost our immune systems because moms don’t get sick days! i even made one for huddy with just 3 drops of thieves! 
diffusing thieves purifies the air of germs and smells like christmas! what more could you want? 💁🏼 my favorite way to diffuse this is with lemon after cooking it gets rid of that yucky food smell that tends to linger after a meal. you can also put thieves and lemon in your tea with honey for an extra immune boost when you’re feeling cruddy! 
also in your kit you get a sample  of thieves cleaner that makes a whole bottle! it seriously is so so good, it has replaced all of my other cleaners in my house! it is 100% natural, plant-based and works great on every surface from glass to floors! i also love how safe it is to use around my little! the bottle says if consumed just drink water. no poison control need here! that just blows my mind! 😱this makes me feel so good as a mom that i don’t have to worry about hudson getting into the cleaner and hurting himself! 
what is your fave way to use thieves?
.
.
.
.

text:
my mood since wednesday. i've been running so hard the last few months, working on something big almost every day. 
i am grateful to be busy with the work i love most in the world. 
____

but after a very emotionally exhausting photo shoot the other day (dealing with the kind of men who just don't get why the #metoo movement matters) and the arrival of my monthly hormonal flux (yep, we can say that because it's a normal part of life and not tmi), my body which was already tired just needed to be horizontal.

____

i remembered back to earlier this year when i could hardly move off the couch and how i learned that i needed time to do nothing so my soul and body could repair.

____

and i promised that i would give myself that without having to be taken down first.

____

i heated up some soup i'd made a few nights before, drank a glass of (organic red) wine and with gingie perfectly positioned against my stomach, we watched crap tv.

____

i know that it would be better if i would post curated photos, and promote the stuff i have coming up (there's lots), but that just doesn't feel like where i'm at at the moment. so you get this. it's real. 
___

and isn't it nice to see just a normal human doing normal things (practicing the self-care she preaches) with her cat? 🤣😂😁

text:
je viens de vivre l’une des plus belles expériences de ma vie. 
ce soir, je suis allée à la rencontre de futurs intervenants, dans un cours de sexologie, à l’université , pour leur parler de mon agression en juin. de comment j’ai passé au travers, de ma perception de mon corps, sexualité, de ma façon de vivre chaque jour etc. jamais j’avais été capable d’en parler librement devant des gens devant moi sans peur du jugement, colère etc. j’ai sentie une immense vague d’amour mais surtout d’écoute, de compassion et d’aucun jugement. une vague de gens qui veulent vraiment comprendre afin de bien aider leur prochain. j’ai l’impression que toute la pression sur mes épaules que j’avais avec cela, vient de tomber. j’ai sentie en sortant de la classe, que la boucle de cette histoire vient vraiment de se fermer. j’ai eu la chance de répondre à leurs questions pendant 1h. ce fût tellement un échange extraordinaire. merci diane de m’avoir invitée et avoir pensée à moi! merci à tous les étudiants, vous n’avez pas idée le bien que vous m’avez faites. xxxxx

text_retweet:
we are so excited to share the news!! be sure to catch tina’s podcast release november 29th at 3pm!! give her a follow to stay updated on the release! #repost @thattinacorn ・・・
💫okay you guys. i know i have been dropping hints talking about this project i am working on. i am so excited to finally announce... i am starting a podcast!💫 my dream has transformed over the past year and i am making huge steps towards my ultimate goal. naming jane doe is a platform for survivors of sex trafficking to take back their identity and use their most powerful tool, their voice, to inform the public about their journey after the game. we are not dirty, helpless charity cases that need saving. we need understanding and opportunity. when faced with the option to grow and achieve, we excel. we use the lessons we learned in the life to rise, and rise we do. 
drop a 👑 if you want the link to my first podcast when it drops! thank you to @breakingfreemn for supporting this dream and opening up more lines of communication and ultimately, hope. 💜
.
.

text:
this weeks article was inspired by last month's first year anniversary of the public #metoo movement.
my message is this: ➡️ it is never too late to tell.⬅️ last month when many national articles and social media quotes and thoughts were posted about what this past year has been like, i sat down and wrote out my 2 cents. should i have posted this that same day when everyone else was doing it? yes, but i decided to wait because every single day, more women all over the world has experienced there own new me too story. 
this new @ladieslifeguide article (🔗link in bio 👆) is reminder that when you tell your story, you are not only going to help heal yourself, but you are prevented to possibly saving another woman from experiencing it also. 🌺
so if you're 15 years old, 25, 35 or 45 or even 75 and beyond & every single age in between - please know that no what age you are, no matter what age you were when it happened and no matter how long ago -  it doesn't matter - 
you can still tell.
i know this take immense courage and strength. sharing your story might even inspire others to tell. women are truly powerful and we deserve to be heard, believed and supported. even when so many women have had these horrific experiences, we carry on and we find our strength again. when you come out the other side you will look back and see how you had more strength and courage that you ever thought you did. i know it is scary but you are worth it. your story is worth to be heard. your healing is worth it and your peace of mind and soul are worth it. 🌟
i hope you read it and share it to someone who you know needs this reminder. i hope you continue to have this conversation with those who need to be reminded. always remember that you are loved, supported & believed. 💕
~

text:
getting to share this work again with everyone in st.petersburg, fl the past three months was awesome! i’m so happy at a time when women’s stories are needed more than ever that i got to share this body of work again because it speaks so much to the voices of women, voices that are not heard, suppressed, and revealing truth to people. in everything i do, it’s about giving a voice to the voiceless, it can be another person and sometimes it’s myself too. i’m constantly working on being comfortable with my own voice, this past year i’ve taken some steps to challenge myself. one was writing my first feature length screenplay. it’s my total focus right now and i plan to take it all the way to the screen. i hope to make even more strides to openly express myself and feel comfortable being overt with people, to not just visualize, but to verbalize my thoughts for people to read and hear.
.
.
.

text:
unfortunately, false accusations of rape are just as common as rape itself. false accusers are malicious and terrible human beings that ruin the lives of their victims, they are criminals and should be treated as such. stop trying to use the stories of real rape victims as a scapegoat to justify using sexual assault accusations as a weapon against someone! ( i am not referring to actual rape victims, i am strictly talking about liars) 
people who experience being called out for an assault that in fact did not happen often have to succumb to severe bullying, family disownment, loss or rejection of job, a ruined reputation, depression/anxiety, and the list goes on. some even go so far as to commit suicide! we must protect our brothers, father's, friends, husbands, boyfriends, etc. from this madness by bringing awareness to false rape accusations! 
#himtoo #metoo #radicalfeminism #rape
no i do not #believeallwomen

text: today is my 2 year anniversary of beating hepatitis c.  for 15 years i struggled with body aches, head aches, tiredness, brain fog, and also the stigma of the uneducated prejudice.  i failed my first treatment go around 12 years ago. for 6 weeks we hoped while i took injections that made me so sick. only to be told the treatment wasn’t working.  i applied a few other times to studies only to be told i didn’t qualify because a: i wasn’t sick enough to try it.  b: because it would work for me because i had the geno type 1 which was resistance to treatment.  finally a friend who is a dr went to a seminar to find out about hep c and the cures.  after applying again for a year to get in to a new treatment program being rejected getting discouraged trying again over and over i gave up.  that day i received a letter telling me i qualified!! i did 12 weeks of treatment and now have been officially cured for two years!! i have kept my story a secret because of the judgement and condemnation of hep c. education a person doesn’t have to have been a drug user to have it.  a person can have it and never know.  it is not routinely tested for except in pregnant women in a few states like florida.  transparency is important and this is me going first!  #hepc #hepccured #hepceducation #metoo #mefirst #weallhaveastory

#repostfrom from @enambelasffest
.
@tatyanaakman /// hampir semua orang yang kukenal pernah mengalami kekerasan berbasis gender, hal ini seringkali nggak dianggap serius, lebih sering di abaikan dan ditaruh jauh-jauh di belakang kepala dan hati masing-masing. maybe thats how we've been raised, at least that's how i've been raised, to keep quiet about it, "yang waras ngalah deh". enak aja!
•
makanya terlepas dari apapun profesi, gender, dan latar belakangnya, anak muda harus ikut andil dalam mengkampanyekan #hearmetoo dalam mengakhiri kekerasan berbasis gender. banyak yang bisa kita lakukan melalui karya-karya seni seperti film, lagu, lukisan, gambar, video pendek, maupun tulisan. pokoknya apapun bentuknya, mari kita ciptakan indonesia yang bebas dari kekerasan berbasis gender melalui karya-karya kita.
.
selain itu, teman-teman bisa mendukung agenda kampanye #enambelasffest @enambelasffest dengan menghadiri pemutaran film sepanjang #16haktp mulai tanggal 25 november besok! tema tahun ini adalah #hearmetoo dimana kami mengajak teman-teman untuk memberikan wadah yang aman dan dukungan yang positif, serta mendengarkan cerita-cerita para korban dan penyintas kekerasan berbasis gender.
.
.

text:
i jump at the sound of my phone
eager to be the recipient of answers to what's unknown
i don't have the answer, but the answer will come
i tell myself from the moment i wake up until the day is done.
it's been months.

it's unbearable, unsustainable, indescribable, too complainable
and i'm barely holding on and my lawyer's on retainer and i'm never gonna win and that's only getting plainer
but i keep on persevering because the fight gives my life meaning

and it's killing me slowly
but at least i'm not confused anymore
though admitting i was abused has been
thoroughly utterly debilitating
as has coming forward to accuse him of it
and watching him get excused for it
it never does get easier
instead i just get used to it

text: #tbt to #panther being released 1 year ago today ✨🐾 we released this right in the midst of the #metoo conversation and wow, we have come so far...as individuals, as a partnership, as well as a collective and as a country. i am disheartened on the daily by the state of affairs with trump as president but so much has been fired up that can not be extinguished. this movement sparked hard conversations - brave womxn came forward to share dark secrets & blurry shameful memories. we dug down deep, split wide open, and asked for compassion. raw and sad, painful and vulnerable... and that made space to heal...together 🌊they are gonna keep coming after us, after whatever rights and power this sick administration can threaten but i’m not worried. we will fight harder, fairer, and freer than ever before. we are carrying the weight of the world right now but that’s only making us stronger. we are the panthers not the prey 🐆 there is a better way and we are demanding it together ✊🏻✊🏼✊🏽✊🏾✊🏿

text:
i was just interviewed on the your mark on the world podcast. @devindthorpe is an amazing force in the world and i’m honored he asked me to be in his podcast.  here’s what he said, “leta greene is such a happy person that virtually no one knew the story of her childhood. she liked it that way. she was proud of that! 
recently, however, she felt compelled to share her story on facebook. her community rallied to support her and a publisher offered to publish a book. 
the book, love, me too, is out. i talked to leta about her experience and the insights in her book. you don't want to miss this special episode.” #metoo #childabuse #devtalk

મુંબઈઃ બોલિવૂડની સૌથી લોકપ્રિય જોડીમાં શાહરૂખ-કાજોલનો સમાવેશ થાય છે. બંને વચ્ચે સારી કેમેસ્ટ્રી જોવા મળે છે. કાજોલે હાલમાં જ એક પ્રોગ્રામમાં ખુલાસો કર્યો હતો કે શૂટિંગ સમયે શાહરૂખ ઘણી જ મસ્તી કરે છે. કાજોલે 'દિલવાલે દુલ્હનિયા લે જાયેંગે'નો એક કિસ્સો શૅર કર્યો હતો. કાજોલે કહ્યું હતું કે આ ફિલ્મના શૂટિંગ દરમિયાન શાહરૂખ ખાને તેને નીચે પાડી દીધી હતી. કાજોલે એમ પણ કહ્યું હતું કે શાહરૂખે જે મસ્તીઓ કરી છે, તેની સાથે, તેને લઈને તેની પર કેસ ચાલવો જોઈએ.

text:
@regran_ed from @madfuckingwitches -  day 315. another woman was violently killed in australia two days ago, witches. maria van beers, aged 63, was allegedly stabbed to death by her ex-husband in tweed heads. worst of all, she’d just appealed for help and had just the previous day taken out an avo against him. 
how fucking terrified must poor maria have been. and how fucking alone. did you hear about her horrific death? no? it’s not surprising. unless you follow sites like the red heart campaign who document these murders, or unless you live locally where this was well reported, you wouldn’t know. we found some local sites and a channel 9 link, but apart from that, fucking *crickets*. at the risk of sounding like stuck fucking records, we once again bring up the fucking bullshit hypocrisy here. if a shark attack had occurred anywhere in the country a few days ago, it would’ve been front page fucking news. if a muslim had killed someone it’d be the first 10 pages and the number one tv news report. if another needle had been found in any kind of fruit, we’d be sick of fucking hearing about it. and not only the reporting, but the fucking money thrown at fixing it. nothing too much trouble. no fucking expense spared. and no politician unwilling to smirk at a camera for extra brownie points. 
women. stabbed, strangled, drowned, raped, burned, shot, gassed or bludgeoned. with or without their children. by partners or strangers. terrorised for years or taken by surprise. young or old, attractive or not, disabled or not, rich or poor or middling, gay or straight, partnered or not, happy, sad, mothers, non-mothers. all valuable. all special. all alive, until they weren’t. all suffering intense fear and pain, until it stopped. and almost all killed by men both known and unknown to them. 
we’ll say it again: lock the fucking men up till they find a way to prove we’re safe from them. lock them up before one more woman fucking dies. lock them up because why the fuck are they free while women - all women - must be careful? #lockupthemen #metoo - #regrann

text: kilpaurheilulla ei välttämättä ole tekemistä terveellisyyden kanssa, se on raakaa ja siihen kuuluu itsensä ylittäminen ja överit, jotka tavalliselle talliaiselle olis jopa vaarallisia. tämän ymmärrän. sen sijaan en ymmärrä, että nöyryyttämisestä, pelolla valmentamisesta ja lapsista puhutaan samassa virkkeessä, kuten urheilulehden jutussa joukkuevoimistelun valmennuksesta. juttu antoi kuvan vääristyneestä lajikulttuurista. moni on tiennyt ja hiljaisesti hyväksynyt käytetyt valmennusmetodit. se antaa kuvan, että vain kovat menestyvät. muut tippuvat kelkasta. ei väliä, vaikka vähän (tai paljon) vaurioituneinakin tai vaikka heillä olisi urheilullisia edellytyksiä. - itselläni ei ole kilpaurheilutaustaa, mutta eikö motivoituneita urheilijoita pysty tsemppaamaan parhaaseensa positiivisen kautta? tarvitaanko alistamista ja nöyryyttämistä? tää kuvio muistuttaa #metoo'sta. molemmissa on kyse vallankäytöstä ja varmaan myös siitä, että (tässä tapauksessa) valmentajan oma menestyksenjano ajaa ohi urheilijan terveydestä ja hyvinvoinnista. tämä juttu oli tärkeä avaus urheilulehdeltä. asioita voidaan muuttaa vain avoimuuden kautta. #urheilulehti #voimisteluliitto #syömishäiriö #joukkuevoimistelu #valmennus @syomishairioliitto #pjhommia

at a rally in dublin on wednesday, tara brown of the national women’s council of ireland said: “we stand in solidarity with survivors of sexual assault who are being grievously failed by our criminal justice system. the type of clothes a victim was wearing has no place in our criminal justice system, and it had no place in determining what is consent.

we have a responsibility to create a safe system for survivors of sexual assault, and we are repeatedly shown that we are a long way from achieving a victim-centred [prosecution] system.

text:
«токсичный» год или как язык описывает реальность. ⠀
словом года по версии оксфордского словаря стало «toxic». используемый в различных контекстах он одновременно означает: ядовитый, токсичный, угрожающий жизни. данное слово на протяжение 2018 года употреблялось не только применительно к сфере химии или экологии, но также описывая те или иные формы отношений. 
в частности, во многом благодаря кампании #metoo появилось выражение «токсчичная маскулинность», обозначающая пренебрежительное, доминирующее и часто насильственное отношение, как правило, мужчин по отношению к другим гендерным субъектам (женщинам, гомосексуалам, трансгендерам).
⠀
"слово года" - это ежегодная акция, которая проводится в различных странах мира, направленная на выявление наиболее распространенных и чаще всего запрашиваемых и цитируемых слов и их сочетаний. существует британская и американская версия «слова года», являющиеся наиболее популярными сегодня. ⠀
то, что слово «токсичный» чаще всего цитировали и запрашивали пользователи оксфордского словаря не только в прямом значении (ядовитый), но и в переносном применительно к социальной сфере, позволяет через язык определить проблемные точки современного общества, среди которых гендерная повестка и проблема насилия остаются одними из топовых.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
"what do you do if your work is not considered work and you are not considered a person? will the sexual harassment against you be acknowledged?

as a member of the domestic workers union pointed out, the rape of minor girls (maids) almost never makes it to the mainstream news. “there have been cases where the girl is raped, murdered and buried in the compound of the house she works in and no one knows she’s missing until weeks, sometimes months later.” to tackle at least part of the problem, the domestic workers union has been demanding the presence of an icc in the apartment blocks." read the full article: link in bio.

text: na een lange week werken is het tijd om dit weekend languit op te bank te liggen met netflix (en misschien wel een goed glas wijn). maar in plaats van dat je game of thrones aanzet of nog een keer besluit om gossip girl te bingewatchen, kan je ook kiezen voor een goede documentaire. het fijne aan biografische documentaires is dat het hele leven van de hoofdpersoon wordt blootgesteld aan de camera: van fuck-ups tot successen. dit geeft jou weer een boost aan inspiratie en energie om komende week aan de slag te gaan. de documentaire ‘seeing allred’ is wat ons betreft een must see. de docu gaat over gloria allred, die haar leven en carrière in het teken heeft gezet van één ding: de rechten van vrouwen. sommigen zien haar als een bitse feministe, maar voor anderen is zij de meest onverschrokken vrouwenrechtenadvocaat van amerika. gloria stond op tegen het partnergeweld in de o.j. simpson zaak en gaat de strijd aan tegen seksuele intimidatie met de #metoo beweging. haar verschijning is intimiderend en tegelijkertijd inspirerend. na het zien van de documentaire zul je het gevoel hebben dat je, net als gloria, de hele wereld aankan. heb jij deze inspirerende docu al bekeken? 📷@ariellevey #businessbabesnl #thegoaldiggersclub #empoweringwomen #inspiration

text:
le donne, così preziose quanto fragili. ogni giorno, nel mondo, molte donne subiscono violenze e vengono uccise. poche sono quelle che trovano il coraggio di denunciare, molte quelle che decidono di non parlare. una “storia” che prosegue da decenni ma che ancora non smette di cessare. il 25 novembre è la giornata mondiale contro la violenza sulle donne, una data importante che va onorata sempre e non solo in un determinato periodo. infatti, per noi è sempre 25 novembre, così come per @sorgeniaofficial , sostenitore credibile della causa femminile che sprona a reagire dinanzi a tanto orrore, trasmettendo quell’energia in più per parlare e non restare mai in silenzio. la campagna #sempre25novembre si impegna affinchè la violenza sulle donne cessa di esistere non solo per un giorno, ma per sempre. è possibile donare un piccolo contributo con una semplice foto (selfie) contenente il numero “25” e ampliare questa iniziativa per trasmetterla ad un numero sempre maggiore di persone. anche un solo scatto puó fare una differenza. non restare il silenzio, ogni giorno è 25 novembre! 🌹🎀 •
•
•
•
•
•
•
#ad #violenzasulledonne #metoo #girlpower #strongwoman #strongwomen #womanpower #womerpower #energypeople #sorgenia #bestrong #giornatamondialecontrolaviolenzasulledonne #25novembre

text:
for those 87 million people probably wondering what was actually done with their data, i went back to christopher wylie, the ex-cambridge analytica employee who blew the whistle on the company’s problematic operations in the observer. according to wylie, all you need to know is a little bit about data science, a little bit about bored rich women, and a little bit about human psychology.

step one, he says, over the phone as he scrambles to catch a train: - when you’re building an algorithm, you first need to create a training set. that is: no matter what you want to use fancy data science to discover, you first need to gather the old-fashioned way. before you can use facebook likes to predict a person’s psychological profile, you need to get a few hundred thousand people to do a 120-question personality quiz.

the “training set” refers, then, to that data in its entirety: the facebook likes, the personality tests, and everything else you want to learn from. most important, it needs to contain your “feature set”: - the underlying data that you want to make predictions on, wylie says. - in this case, it’s facebook data, but it could be, for example, text, like natural language, or it could be clickstream data – the complete record of your browsing activity on the web. - those are all the features that you want to [use to] predict. at the other end, you need your target variables, the things that you’re trying to predict for. so in this case, personality traits or political orientation, or what have you.

alex hern
the guardian

text:
this poem was written in the 1800’s by william ross wallace, and still rings true today.  more powerful, or rather more disillusioning words are rarely spoken.

most of the issues we are so fervently protesting, advocating and pushing to change, are born and bred in our own homes.

remember the saying “charity begins at home” ? well, change does too. 
#racism #metoo #rape #abuse #victimization #entitlement #blacklivesmatter #whitelivesmatter #guncontrol #bullying  #stopbullying #meangirls #gossiping #addiction #selfesteem #boundaries #respect 
as a mom of boys, i am reminded daily that i play a large role in shaping their view of the world and their view of themselves.

these are the foundational moments.

a mother can make or break her son, his wife, their family. we need to seize teachable moments to show our boys to set boundaries, respect boundaries and respect differences.

women easily forget that our roles, and the connection we keep with our maker, holds the power to make this world a little less broken. 🖤

sebagai seorang ibu, saya mengharapkan anak saya, dan para perempuan indonesia, dapat tumbuh dan menjalani hidup di indonesia dengan aman dan bebas dari kekerasan berbasis gender. 
selama 16 hari anti kekerasan terhadap perempuan, saya mengajak masyarakat memberikan dukungan penuh dan mengikuti agenda kegiatan kampanye dari @enambelasffestival .

ada banyak wadah kita mendukung kampanye #hearmetoo seperti penayangan film, diskusi, pameran, dan pementasan yang sangat mengedukasi kita mengenai kekerasan seksual dan kekerasan terhadap perempuan mulai tanggal 25 november hingga 10 desember 2018. ///

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
cw: przemoc seksualna.

w irlandii sąd uniewinnił 27-letniego mężczyznę oskarżonego o gwałt. za dowód jego niewinności uznano… koronkowe majtki, które miała na sobie siedemnastolatka, którą zgwałcił, a które według adwokatki oskarżonego sugerowały, że ofiara „chciała kogoś spotkać” (i w domyśle – uprawiać seks). (tak, to była adwokatka – ten argument zaprezentowała kobieta).
.
to niestety nie jest odosobniony przypadek. i nie tylko sądy obarczają winą ofiary, a nie sprawców. to samo robią codziennie całe masy osób, które pozwalają sobie na komentarze typu „w takiej miniówie to czego się spodziewała?”, „z takim dekoltem? wiadomo, że sama tego chciała”, „jak się tak odstawia, to niech się potem nie dziwi”. obwinianie osoby doświadczającej przemocy i usprawiedliwianie sprawców ma się świetnie.
.
niestety nadal doświadczamy też konsekwencji tego, jak różnie i jak często absurdalnie, definiowana jest zgoda. w szwecji przeprowadzono ostatnio badania na temat tego, jak osoby w wieku 18-25 lat interpretują zgodę. okazało się, że dla 33% mężczyzn zgodą było… leżenie nago z drugą osobą (wśród kobiet tę samą odpowiedź podało 16% respondentek). 17% mężczyzn uznało, że zgodą jest pójście z kimś późno wieczorem do domu (wśród kobiet było to 7% – różnice są znamienne).
.
ciągle musimy walczyć o to, by dla wszystkich stało się jasne, że zgoda ma być wyraźna i dobrowolna, ze wszystkich stron. i że winnym gwałtu jest zawsze gwałciciel – nigdy ofiara, nigdy ubranie, nigdy jego brak, nigdy wypity drink. #thisisnotconsent #ibelieveher #metoo #endrapeculture #stopkulturzegwałtu [o sprawie w irlandii czytałam na wysokieobcasy.pl i irishexaminer.com, a dane ze szwecji pochodzą ze strony svt.se]

text:
\\
left for sale
.
i set out on a journey
alone,
and unassisted;
to explore the world,
in a hope
to find myself.

what remained
i couldn't understand
and couldn't explain.
or perhaps
didn't want to accept.

just an item,
a commodity.
or to subtly say,
a thing of beauty.

all along the trail
that i made;
in the end
i found myself,
left for sale.
~a
.

this shot captures the rangoli made by the students of rk hall of residence, iit kharagpur for the festival of illumination that took place on the occasion of diwali in october 2018. this particular rangoli is a set of 6 rangolis, all made under the similar concept and theme.

text:
from tarana burke (founder of the ‘me too’ movement) to luong ung (author of “first they killed my father, now a netflix film by angeline jolie) to gill hicks (peace activist & survivor of london train bombing) and many more, women’s leadership day at facebook has been nothing short of inspiring and thought provoking. 
the stories of these amazing women who did not let their circumstances limit them, but instead fiercely rose from the ashes and made immense impact through sheer grit, unwavering determination and courage, left me hungry to do more, contribute more, and impact more people around me. 
thank you for your courage, thank you for being such great role models, thank you for telling us that we all have the potential to achieve something amazing. 
and indeed, we are stronger together.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
\\
under the weight of things
.
under the weight of things;
unknown
and unseen.
she knows
he would lead her,
right where she needs to be.

but then,
who knew
it was all nothing,
but a sham!

she could never return.
for he took her
under the weight of things;
unknown
and unseen.
~a
.

text:
\\
the trade of pain
.
its been like this
since
i don't know when;
it seems forever to me now.

thousand words
i wanted to say.
i thought
he would listen.

he gave excuses,
for days
and weeks
and months
and years.

hoping
that this would change,
i waited
and waited.

one fine day
it occurred to me;
it was just the pain
that i traded
for his happiness.
~a
.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
jury duty: ojojoj! legenderna christina knight (@byknight) viktoria saxby (@goodnewseverywhere) kommer på söndag sitta i juryn! de driver tillsammans @timefor_taketwo som har som mål att skapa en mer representativ mediebransch med ökad jämställdhet och mångfald. dessa två personer har extremt många järn i elden, med ett tydligt fokus.
.
viktoria har 25 års erfarenhet av jämställdhetsarbete, och 15 års erfarenhet av att arbeta med maskulinitetsfrågor. genom hennes organisation hopeexhibit har hon skapat globala fotoutställningar och kampanjer för att engagera män och pojkar för jämställdhet för bl.a. fn och världsbanken, samt medverkat till att skapa den globala kampanjen men-care.org. hon har även arbetat i 6 år som jämställdhetspolitiskt sakkunnig i svensk politik. viktoria kommer våren 2019 ut med boken: den nya mannen: om pojkar, män och slutet på könskampen.
.
christina gav 2013 ut den uppmärksammade boken "mad women – a herstory of advertising" vilket drog igång en välgörande och uppskattad diskussion i mediabranschen kring representation och bristen på mångfald. våren 2018 kom uppföljaren "not buying it", en praktisk handbok i allt från att hantera sexuella trakasserier och härskartekniker till hur en bäst löneförhandlar och kommer tillbaka efter en föräldraledighet. christina sitter i styrelsen för bl a fredrika bremer förbundet, international alliance of women och wateraid. christina har jobbat med kommunikation i över 30 år och är en av den svenska reklambranschens få kvinnliga creative directors.
.
stort tack viktoria och christina för att ni tar plats i #nowwhat jury! #sthlmtech #norrsken #metoo

text:
一名前教練涉嫌於約8年前藉詞為女學員按摩，把她帶到自己家中猥褻侵犯。案件在裁判法院裁決，前教練被裁定非禮罪名不成立。雖然未能入罪，但官亦讚揚當事人的勇氣極之值得欣賞。 
事實上，報警與上庭並不是所有性侵案爭取公義的出口，更不是受害人的唯一選擇。在疑點利益歸於被告的法律制度下，法庭判決背後的考慮因素有許多，而當中也混雜很多對性暴力受害者的迷思，例如當下為何不反抗、事後和被告保持聯繫等等。法庭和法律似乎是法治和公義的象徵，但法律制度有它自身的限制，主任裁判官練錦鴻裁決時亦指出，法庭的裁決「非一定是事實的反映」，是基於多項疑點，才裁定被告無罪。因此法庭裁決不成立並不等於當事人是誣告，希望社會大眾明白這一點，停止在受害人傷口上灑鹽。
裁判官亦認為當事人挺身把舊事公開的行為「極之值得讚揚」，指當事人的行為勇敢及無私。儘管法庭的判決令人失望，我們亦想感謝當事人承受著巨大的壓力，說出自己的經歷；過去一年她受到 #metoo 運動啟發，早前曾在社交平台勇敢地公開性侵經歷，從網絡到走入法庭，一路披荊斬棘，她的勇敢和努力的確激勵了許多受害人發聲與求助。

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
teaching diaries 101.

chapter - gratitude

lesson - count the blessings

research question - is life too short?

aims -

1. to meet people who are up for meaningful conversations
2. to imbibe all the goodness they have to offer 
3. to learn different perspectives

summary - 
met mrs. & mr. nair after ages. aunty is 84 years young, she gave me a call after she read my book; after having spoken to her, had to meet her in person. 
although i was lost in my own world where i was taking care of 'things', my dad reminded me that i had to meet her and so i go to their place with bitter chocolates and grapefruit champagne - but come back with a fuller heart and mind.

from talking about politics, to places, to death, to the meaning of life, to the #metoo movement, to hypocrisy, to freedom of choice, to crotchet, future plans, different books and various phases of life - it felt like the entire meeting transitioned and felt whole.

what touched or rather moved me was this 84 year old beautiful lady, who was one of the first women to be an engineer telling me that she keeps my book by her pillow and reads it every day. the chapter she chooses to read depends on her mood that very day.

i, for most of my life cribbed about the absence of transparency, perspective and bonds with the elderly or other relatives of my family and in just one day experienced it all.

now the question could be why now or the answer could be 'no time like the present'

homework -
1. meet more people, as many as i can
2. talk openly rather often
3. travel a little more

#lessons #peopleinthe_world #chasingemotions #movingconversations #thatsthat #onelife #dreams #words

text:
on 16 october, a year after an indian woman journalist wrote about her harrowing experience of sexual harassment by her then-editor and now former minister mobashar jawed akbar, he stepped down from his position within the ruling bharatiya janata party (bjp). his resignation came after the journalist, priya ramani, revealed his name on twitter, spurring more victims of akbar’s to reveal his predatory advances under the #metoo hashtag.

this shows that the global, women-led #metoo movement is finally gaining traction in asia, as women across the region speak out against deeply-entrenched inequalities and address problems of violence against women.

here in singapore, corinna lim, executive director of singapore’s leading gender equality advocacy group association of women for action and research (aware). saw a 79 per cent increase in the number of people reaching out aware in late 2017.

read about "how women in asia are marching to #metoo" by zafirah zein in our bio link!

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green, author
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
canção do bandido | ópera
teatro da trindade | 8 a 18 de novembro
qua 19h | qui e sáb 21h | dom 16h30

música & direcção musical nuno côrte-real
libreto pedro mexia
encenação ricardo neves-neves

cantores andré henriques, bárbara barradas, cátia moreso, inês simões, marco alves dos santos e sónia alcobaça
coro do teatro nacional de são carlos e orquestra sinfónica portuguesa

cenário henrique ralheta
figurinos rafaela mapril 
desenho de luz luís duarte 
assistência de encenação rafael gomes e diana vaz

produção executiva força de produção
coprodução teatro da trindade inatel, teatro nacional de são carlos e temporada darcos

partindo do conto tradicional o macaco de rabo cortado, canção do bandido imagina uma personagem que não é um macaco mas um advogado, casanova dos tempos modernos, homem que acumula conquistas e as vai trocando por novas conquistas, sem pensar muito nas consequências dos seus atos. 
o casanovismo e o donjuanismo são revisitados numa época em que as guerras dos sexos (ou dos géneros) já não são o que eram, ou têm pelo menos discursos e legitimidades diferentes. coros gregos e essencialismos em tempos digitais e de #metoo? em quem devemos acreditar: no libreto, nos protagonistas, nos antagonistas, ou nas personagens que, falando em vez de cantar, contestam estes diálogos, estes tipos, esta dialética? 
de d. giovanni à música pop, dos bordões linguísticos aos jogos nonsense, as personagens de «canção do bandido» trazem para o palco tudo o que lhes ocorre, tudo o que sirva as suas estratégias ou ilustra as suas dúvidas. e os espectadores, certamente, tomam partido.

text:
the google walkout is the latest demonstration of the power that employees have when coming together to voice concerns on an issue. as the movement gathered pace so too did the pressure on the company to review its policies and put in better protections for employees.

with an estimated 35% of women globally experiencing sexual harassment at work its important that major companies lead the way with ensuring a safe working environment for everyone.

in the aftermath we’re left with more questions about gender equality, not just in tech but the business community in general. @worldeconomicforum suggests that if we carry on moving at current rates of progression then the economic gender gap will take more than 200 years to close.

what should we be doing to bring about true equality at a faster pace?

text:
which pair do i wear not to be raped. after a 17 year olds underwear was used as evidence in a rape trial to show her "consent" or willingness to be raped i find myself hurt in my soul. why in this day and age are we still being blamed for other people's actions for wearing an item of clothing? the color shape or material are not verbal consent of "yes i want you" they are a choice of mood circumstance or convenience. if i wore a snorkel would you drown me if i decided not to swim because i wore something with intention?

#ibelieveher #metoo #clothingisnotconsent
#thisisnotconsent #nomeansno #stillnotaskingforit

text:
a very special issue of the caravan magazine. the reckoning is our effort to bring to fore stories of sexual harassment and abuse of power, especially relevant in light of the recent allegations that have surfaced as part of the metoo movement in india. 
this issue will be one of the most memorable ones for me in the magazine. i am so grateful to all the women who came forward to trust us with their stories and have the courage of speaking truth to power. 
i had the fabulous opportunity of working with an all female powerhouse crew of illustrators for the issue.

cover illustration by the amazing suzanne dias, who was so great to work with. 
if you believe in the cause, do buy a copy. now out on stands and amazon. if you would like to support our journalism, please do subscribe! link in bio. 
#caravanmagazine #thecaravanmagazine #metoo #women #sexualharassment #coverjunkie

text:
hello everybody! anyone who has been following the #thisisnotconsent movement will be familar with the cork sexual violence center, and the work their doing for this movement. they need volunteers, as much or as little time you can give would be appreciated. this is a hugely important movement, and has probably effected majority of people, either personally or through someone else they may know. please contact them as stated in the picture, its such a great thing to be involved with guys and coming up to xmas, its all about giving! so lets join forces, men, women, adults and children, lets stand together and help debunk rape myths and completly get rid of victim blaming. 
if anyone at all has a few hours to spare, i promise this is a worthwhile cause! 
anyone unfamiliar with this movement please feel free to contact me or anyone else involved and im sure we can help everybody understand what this campaign is about! 
rape is never the victims fault, and no human should ever be made feel it is! 
thank you all x 
#thisisnotconsent
#rapemythsdebunked 
#cork 
#nomeansno 
#metoo 
#metoomovement

text_retweet:
#repost from @zeit 
heute, november 2018:
alle sind so fröhlich. das politikerinnenselfie, aufgenommen auf dem festakt zur einführung des frauenwahlrechts vor 100 jahren, zeigt strotzenden optimismus. warum auch nicht? mag die geschichte auch hin und her wogen, die zukunft wird weiblicher als die vergangenheit sein. jener lächeln manuela schwesig und franziska giffey entgegen, bettina hagedorn, ursula lehr (vorne mitte), angela merkel, christine bergmann und rita süssmuth.

damals, märz 2014:
alle sind so fröhlich. das angeblich berühmteste selfie der welt, auf dem sich am rande der oscar-verleihung diverse hollywoodstars drängeln, stammt aus einer vergangenheit, in der ihre welt noch in ordnung zu sein schien. aus der zeit vor #metoo und donald trump grüßen jennifer lawrence, channing tatum, meryl streep, julia roberts, ellen degeneres, brad pitt, bradley cooper – und ganz hinten sogar kevin spacey, mit dem heute vermutlich keiner der anderen stars mehr ein selfie machen würde. #heutedamals #heuteunddamals #throwback #zeitprint #selfie #politics #angelamerkel #ellendegeneres #oscars #womenvoting #frauenwahlrecht #100jahrefrauenwahlrecht #nowandthen

fotos: heute: manuela schwesig/staatskanzlei/dpa; damals (ausschnitt): ddp images
